Dick Gilbert https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dick_Gilbert 0 Dick Gilbert (July 12, 1889 – May 6, 1960), was an American actor mainly associated with the Hal Roach Studios,where he appeared in numerous Our Gang and Laurel and Hardy comedies. He appeared in 52 films between 1922 and 1951. A former boxer, Gilbert was born in Knox County, Kentucky, United States and died in Goldfield, Nevada, age 70.
